\n\n**Recommendation:** Parse once into the struct, then use reflection or a single map unmarshal to detect present fields, rather than individual field unmarshals.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Unnecessary `AbsPath()` Calls with Fallback Pattern**\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go` lines 90-99 and setup.go\n\n**Issue:** \n```go\nsettingsFileAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, EntireSettingsFile)\nif err != nil {\n    settingsFileAbs = EntireSettingsFile  // Fallback to relative\n}\nlocalSettingsFileAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, EntireSettingsLocalFile)\nif err != nil {\n    localSettingsFileAbs = EntireSettingsLocalFile  // Fallback to relative\n}\n```\n\nEach `AbsPath()` calls `WorktreeRoot()`, which runs `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` (a subprocess). When errors occur (e.g., outside repo), this subprocess runs unnecessarily only to be discarded.\n\n**Impact:** Subprocess overhead in error paths. The fallback pattern makes the subprocess call redundant when not in a git repo.\n\n**Recommendation:** Check git repo status first before calling `AbsPath()`, or accept relative paths directly for settings loading.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Repeated File Existence Checks (TOCTOU Anti-pattern)**\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go` lines 269-276 and setup.go\n\n**Issue:** \n```go\nfunc IsSetUp(ctx context.Context) bool {\n    settingsFileAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, EntireSettingsFile)\n    if err != nil {\n        return false\n    }\n    _, err = os.Stat(settingsFileAbs)\n    return err == nil\n}\n```\n\nThen `IsSetUpAndEnabled()` (lines 281-290) calls `IsSetUp()` AND `Load()`:\n- `IsSetUp()` does `os.Stat()` \n- `Load()` does `os.ReadFile()`\n\nTwo filesystem operations for the same file in rapid succession.\n\nSimilarly in setup.go line 123, `IsEmptyRepository()` is called; then if needed, `OpenRepository()` is called again.\n\n**Impact:** Unnecessary filesystem round-trips; potential